README

Aimsir is a clean, fast, and fully static weather website built with HTML, Eleventy, Nunjucks, and Bulma. It is designed as a weather assistant for people in Ireland or visitors to the 6 Irish cities to keep them up to date onIrish weather but also to guide them to suitable activities for the appropriate weather. 

The site provides:

A dashboard showing today’s conditions for all six cities

Individual city pages with a detailed 7‑day forecast

A cohesive visual identity using the Aimsir logo, colour palette, favicon, and consistent component styling

Developer:

This site was developed by Vincent McGRath as part of the Web Design module for the Certificate in Computer Science at SETU 2025

Installation:

-Type cmd in search. Open command prompt window 

-Locate the folder project root and direct in command prompt (cd \project-root)

-npm install (Node.js required to run Eleventy, Bulma, JSON etc.)

-npx @11ty/eleventy --serve (this will run Eleventy)

-Command prompt will show http://localhost:8080

-Paste http://localhost:8080 into Chrome browser 

-Website should now be visible and running locally

-The main site entry point is ‘index.html’ referred to as Dashboard.


Navigation:

The website can be navigated through a menu available within the header.
Th efollowing options are available:

- Dashboard — Main homepage showing today’s weather for all cities

- Cities — Dropdown linking to each of the six individual city pages

- Preferences — Allows users to select their own weather/activity preferences

- Weather Facts — Provides Irish weather facts and links to suitable activities

Navigation is also supported through internal links within pages and the footer.

Technologies Used:

The folowing technologies are incorporated into the

HTML — Structure and content

Eleventy (11ty) — Static site generator

Nunjucks — Templating engine for layouts and components

Bulma — CSS framework for layout and styling

Custom JSON — Hardcoded weather and city data

Modular components — Cards, icons, summaries, banners

Favicon support — /images/aimsirflavicon.png


The Project Structure:

project-root/ 
│ 
├── src/ 
│   ├── _data/            # JSON data (weather data for each city- current & 7day & metadata) 
│   ├── _includes/ 
│   │   ├── components/   # Reusable UI components (headers, footers, icons, cards, summaries) 
│   │   └── layouts/      # Base layouts (base.njk, basics of all site pages) 
│   ├── cities/           # Individual city pages (Each of 6 cities individual pages) 
│   ├── bonus/            # Bonus page (extra page with table + activity cards) 
│   ├── preferences/      # Preferences page (A/B radio button toggles) 
│   ├── css/              # Bulma + custom styling (colour, fonts etc.) 
│   ├── images/           # Weather icons, logo, city images, banners, favicon
│   └── index.njk         # Homepage (Dashboard)
│ 
├── _site/ # Auto‑generated output (do not edit) 
├── .eleventy.js # Eleventy configuration 
└── package.json # Dependencies & scripts


Data Model:

The site uses structured JSON hardcoded data for each city and its weather information.

The following fields are used to retrieve and display this data in a consistent and meaningful way across the site:

slug — This has been used to create URL‑safe city identifier used for banners and links

name — Human‑readable city name

today — Object containing today’s weather, temperature, and wind

forecast — Array of 7 objects (one per day)

weather — Weather description used to map to an icon

temp — Temperature in °C

wind — Wind speed in km/h